# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge
We as members, contributors, and leaders pledge to make participation in our project a harassment-free experience for everyone.

## Our Standards
Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment:
- Using welcoming and inclusive language
- Being respectful of differing viewpoints and experiences
- Gracefully accepting constructive criticism
- Showing empathy towards others

Examples of unacceptable behavior:
- Harassment, trolling, or personal attacks
- Publishing others' private information without permission
- Other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate

## Enforcement Responsibilities
Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying the standards and taking appropriate action when unacceptable behavior occurs.

## Scope
This Code of Conduct applies within all project spaces and in public spaces when representing the project.

## Enforcement
Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by:
- Emailing `bylicki@mail.de`
- Opening a private issue on GitHub

All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

## Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/), version 2.1.
